FBIS4-28795 "dreas114bb_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 INTER-ASIAN AFFAIRS Southeast Asian Nations Hold `Secret Meeting' Southeast Asian Nations Hold `Secret Meeting' BK1006152794 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in English 1400 GMT 10 Jun 94 BK1006152794 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation English BFN [Text] Ten Southeast Asian nations agreed at a secret meeting in Manila last month not to interfere in each other's problem with separatist movements. They are the six ASEAN countries as well as Vietnam, Myanmar [Burma], Laos, and Cambodia. A Philippine official said experts and officials from the 10 countries also discussed laying the groundwork for a regional common market.
